ied lists, steps, and static cards.\\n8. `lib/blueprint-data.ts` — Audited scoring formulas, types, fields, and options.\\n9. `lib/nav-data.ts` & `lib/site-config.ts` — Verified site-wide metadata and path definitions.\\n10. `components/sections/BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx` — Inspected the interactive blueprint generator section.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Audit Findings\\n\\n#### 1. Framework, Routing Model & Styling Stack\\n* **Framework**: Next.js `16.2.9` with React `19.2.4`.\\n* **Routing Model**: Next.js App Router.\\n* **Styling Stack**: Tailwind CSS (version `4.x.x` via `@tailwindcss/postcss`) with variables defined in `app/globals.css`.\\n\\n#### 2. Animation & UI Libraries Availability\\n* **Animation Library**: `motion/react` (version `12.40.0`) is installed and used extensively. The legacy `framer-motion` package is **not** installed.\\n* **Aceternity UI Components**: Only `components/ui/world-map.tsx` and `components/ui/3d_view.tsx` are present in the codebase. No other Aceternity dependencies or component files exist.\\n\\n#### 3. Guardrail Audit (Slug Routings & PublicRoutePage)\\n* **Status: PASS**\\n* **Findings**:\\n  - No `app/[...slug]/page.tsx` file or `app/[...slug]` directory exists.\\n  - No `components/PublicRoutePage.tsx` file exists.\\n  - No imports or code references to `PublicRoutePage` or catch-all slug logic are present in any active page or component.\\n\\n#### 4. Route Gaps (Missing Public Pages)\\n* **Status: GAP IDENTIFIED**\\n* **Findings**:\\n  * Only two routes currently exist as explicit files under `app/`:\\n    - `/` (Home page)\\n    - `/about-us` (About us page)\\n  * All other standard public pages in headers and footers are currently **missing** explicit files in `app/`. The missing route folders are:\\n    - `/capabilities`\\n    - `/platforms`\\n    - `/build`\\n    - `/industries`\\n    - `/why-gff-ai`\\n    - `/company`\\n    - `/resources`\\n    - `/contact`\\n    - `/portal`\\n    - Associated sub-routes (e.g. `/industries/banking`, `/industries/insurance`, `/platforms/blueprint`, `/build/blueprint`, etc.)\\n\\n#### 5. Homepage (Landing Page) Sections Audit\\n* **Status: PASS**\\n* **Findings**:\\n  - All 11 required sections are present and fully integrated:\\n    1. **Hero**: `HeroSection` (Present)\\n    2. **Enterprise Quick Search**: `QuickSearchSection` (Present)\\n    3. **Garage Foundry Factory journey**: `JourneySection` (Present)\\n    4. **What We Build**: `WhatWeBuildSection` (Present)\\n    5. **Interactive Experience**: `InteractiveExperienceSection` (Present)\\n    6. **Global Presence**: `GlobalPresenceSection` (Present)\\n    7. **Client Success**: `ClientSuccessSection` (Present)\\n    8. **Live Dashboard**: `LiveDashboardSection` (Present)\\n    9. **Latest Research**: `LatestResearchSection` (Present)\\n    10. **Contact**: `ContactSection` (Present)\\n    11. **Footer**: `Footer` (Present)\\n  - **Other Active Sections**: `TalkToAgentSection`, `BuildAIEnterpriseSection`, `FoundrySection`, `IndustrySolutionsSection`, `InsightsSection`, `GarageSection`.\\n  - **Anomalies / Observations**: `ProductizedAssetsSection` is imported on line 13 of `components/LandingPage.tsx` but is never rendered inside the JSX.\\n\\n#### 6. Blueprint Scoring Formula & Banking Test Case\\n* **Status: GAP IDENTIFIED**\\n* **Findings**:\\n  - The scoring formula in `lib/blueprint-data.ts` works mathematically based on the weights:\\n    $$\\\\text{Score} = (AI\\\\_Maturity \\\\times 0.20) + (Business\\\\_Need \\\\times 0.25) + (Data\\\\_Readiness \\\\times 0.20) + (Process\\\\_Complexity \\\\times 0.20) + (Transformation\\\\_Readiness \\\\times 0.15)$$\\n  - However, in `components/sections/BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx` (lines 135-141), the scores passed to the formula are currently hardcoded for simulation:\\n    ```typescript\\n    const score = calculateBlueprintScore({\\n      aiMaturityScore: 60,\\n      businessNeedScore: 80,\\n      dataReadinessScore: 50,\\n      processComplexityScore: 50,\\n      transformationReadinessScore: 80\\n    });\\n    ```\\n    This results in a static score of **64** for any answers provided by the user.\\n  - The required Banking test case (**Banking, 15000 employees, Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved**) does not map to dynamic inputs and thus does not return **87/100**.\\n  - **Resolution Need**: In future tasks, we need to map user selections to dynamic maturity values and ensure the specified banking test case evaluates exactly to **87**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Design System Observations\\n* Refined, premium visual styling (dark `#010101` and `#000613` backgrounds, glassmorphism card design, glowing color maps).\\n* Seamless custom SVG iconography, premium gradients (`#E4000F` to `#009DFF`), and balanced responsive layouts.\\n* Clean visual hierarchy adhering strictly to the Apple-like \\\"Apple 2026 Enterprise AI\\\" standard, without excessive badging or generic robot imagery.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Validation Baseline\\n* **Linting**: Passed successfully.\\n* **Static compilation (`npm run build`)**: Compiled successfully in `6.0s` with zero errors.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Recommended Next Task\\n* **Task ID**: `01-safety-cleanup-no-slug-no-publicroutepage` to ensure that any potential routing folders or leftover catch-all directories are completely cleared from the project and that the base explicit App Router folders are clean before adding explicit files. Or proceed immediately to scoring logic alignment under task `10-verify-and-fix-blueprint-generator-scoring`.\"}}\n./automation/logs/2026-06-25T22-42-26-390Z-00-preflight-project-context-implement.log:209:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-25T22:42:25.930Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"reasoning\",\"reasoning\":\"**Confirming Project Stability**\\n\\nI'm incredibly pleased to report that both `npm run lint` and `npm run build` completed successfully, producing zero errors. This indicates a stable codebase and a straightforward build process, which is a significant win.\\n\\n\\n**Analyzing Current Infrastructure**\\n\\nI've just concluded the technical audit. I've discovered the project uses Next.js (v16.2.9) with React (v19.2.4) and employs the Next.js App Router. Styling is handled by Tailwind CSS (v4) with utility classes and custom CSS. Animation is achieved through `motion/react` (v12.40.0). Notably, I've identified significant gaps in the routing model, with several key public pages missing.\\n\\n\\n**Evaluating Routing Compliance**\\n\\nI've been meticulously examining the missing app router files. I can confirm the absence of specific routes, such as `/industries/banking` and `/platforms/blueprint`. I also found that critical `app/[...slug]/page.tsx` and `components/PublicRoutePage.tsx` are missing. These gaps do perfectly align with the prescribed non-negotiable routing constraints, which is a key observation.\\n\\n\\n**Assessing Page Section Hierarchy**\\n\\nI've been examining the section rendering within the landing page. Key sections like `GlobalPresenceSection`, `ClientSuccessSection`, and `ContactSection` are present, but also found extra non-standard sections such as `TalkToAgentSection` and `IndustrySolutionsSection`, which are rendered. I also observed `ProductizedAssetsSection` is imported but not rendered. Furthermore, only two Aceternity UI components exist in the codebase: `world-map.tsx` and `3d_view.tsx`.\\n\\nI've examined the `lib/blueprint-data.ts` file, and confirmed the formula for scoring, as well as test case (banking).\\n\\n\\n**Addressing Blueprint Scoring**\\n\\nI've pinpointed a major flaw in the AI Enterprise section. The `calculateBlueprintScore` function is receiving hardcoded values, resulting in a static score of 64. My \\\"Banking\\\" test case demands an 87/100, which confirms the gap. The generator needs to dynamically map user inputs to maturity scores. I now see my next task is to verify and fix the blueprint generator scoring mechanism, or to perform a final safety cleanup step.\\n\\n\\n\"}}\n./automation/tasks.json:8:    \"prompt\": \"Perform a preflight audit only. Do not edit files. Inspect package.json, app route tree, app/page.tsx, components/LandingPage.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/sections, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/landing-data.ts, lib/blueprint-data.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, and components/CommandCenter.tsx if they exist. Confirm the framework, routing model, styling stack, animation libraries, current page architecture, and whether framer-motion or motion/react is installed. Confirm whether any Aceternity UI components already exist; do not install anything. Check that there is no app/[...slug]/page.tsx and no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx. Search for PublicRoutePage imports and slug catch-all references. Check whether the landing page has all required homepage sections: Hero, Enterprise Quick Search, Garage Foundry Factory journey, What We Build, Interactive Experience, Global Presence, Client Success, Live Dashboard, Latest Research, Contact, Footer. Check whether all public pages are explicit App Router pages. Check whether the Blueprint scoring formula exists and whether the banking test case can return 87/100. Produce a gap list only. Do not edit files. Final response must include files inspected, missing items, route gaps, homepage gaps, design-system observations, animation-library availability, and recommended next task.\"\n./automation/tasks.json:16:    \"prompt\": \"Implement only routing safety cleanup. Remove any forbidden catch-all slug route leftovers. There must be no app/[...slug]/page.tsx, no empty app/[...slug] directory, no components/PublicRoutePage.tsx, and no imports or references to PublicRoutePage. Do not redesign anything. Do not touch the landing page. Ensure all public pages remain explicit App Router pages. If an explicit page is missing, create a minimal explicit page file that uses the existing shared inner-page template, not slug logic. Run lint and build. Acceptance: no module-not-found for PublicRoutePage, no slug route files, no slug references, build passes, landing page unchanged.\"\n","success":true}],"durationMs":1653}}
