cial-services`, `/industries/banking`, `/industries/insurance`, etc.\n    *   **Transformation Tools**: `/build/blueprint`, `/contact` (though currently maps to `/page.tsx#contact` but may require static page routes).\n    *   **Legal / Information**: `/privacy`, `/nda`, `/terms`, `/careers`, `/investors`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Homepage Gaps\n*   **Presence of Required Sections**: The landing page (`components/LandingPage.tsx`) contains all 11 required sections:\n    1.  **Hero** (`HeroSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    2.  **Enterprise Quick Search** (`QuickSearchSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    3.  **Garage Foundry Factory journey** (`JourneySection.tsx`) — Present.\n    4.  **What We Build** (`WhatWeBuildSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    5.  **Interactive Experience** (`InteractiveExperienceSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    6.  **Global Presence** (`GlobalPresenceSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    7.  **Client Success** (`ClientSuccessSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    8.  **Live Dashboard** (`LiveDashboardSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    9.  **Latest Research** (`LatestResearchSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    10. **Contact** (`ContactSection.tsx`) — Present.\n    11. **Footer** (`Footer.tsx`) — Present.\n*   **Extra/Approved Sections**: The landing page also renders several approved high-end sections:\n    *   `TalkToAgentSection.tsx`\n    *   `BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx` (interactive Blueprint generator)\n    *   `FoundrySection.tsx`\n    *   `IndustrySolutionsSection.tsx`\n    *   `InsightsSection.tsx`\n    *   `GarageSection.tsx`\n*   **Homepage Section Gaps/Dead Imports**:\n    *   `ProductizedAssetsSection.tsx` is imported in `components/LandingPage.tsx` but is **not rendered** in the JSX. This is a dead import that can be safely left alone or cleaned up.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Design-System Observations\n*   **Framework**: Next.js App Router (v16.2.9) with React 19.2.4.\n*   **Styling Stack**: Tailwind CSS v4 is configured (`\"tailwindcss\": \"^4\"`, `\"@tailwindcss/postcss\": \"^4\"`). Transition animations are supported by `tw-animate-css` (`^1.4.0`).\n*   **Visual Style**: High-end 2026 enterprise dark mode theme with clean dark backgrounds (`#010101`, `#000613`), custom glowing gradients, and absolute premium styling.\n*   **Aceternity UI Status**: Aceternity UI as a framework library is **not installed** as a whole package, which is perfect for maintaining lightweight and local control. Instead, two custom premium interactive elements inspired by Aceternity UI exist as fully local files:\n    1.  `world-map.tsx`: Uses `dotted-map` to draw beautiful, responsive canvas-like SVG animated vectors representing connections globally.\n    2.  `3d_view.tsx`: Employs HTML5 Canvas with custom logic to draw particle streams mapping GFF network connectivity over a background SVG.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Animation-Library Availability\n*   **Package**: `\"motion\": \"^12.40.0\"` is installed, which represents the new lightweight import for Framer Motion v12.\n*   **Import Style**: Components are importing from `\"motion/react\"` directly (e.g., `import { motion } from \"motion/react\"`). This provides robust hardware-accelerated animations throughout the landing page and map components.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Blueprint Scoring Formula and Banking Test Case\n*   **Scoring Formula Availability**: The correct mathematical scoring formula is defined in `lib/blueprint-data.ts` under `calculateBlueprintScore`:\n    $$\\text{Score} = (0.20 \\times \\text{AI Maturity}) + (0.25 \\times \\text{Business Need}) + (0.20 \\times \\text{Data Readiness}) + (0.20 \\times \\text{Process Complexity}) + (0.15 \\times \\text{Transformation Readiness})$$\n*   **Dynamic Scoring Gap (Critical)**: In `components/sections/BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx`, the inputs from the questionnaire are completely ignored during calculation. The scores are hardcoded to standard static values:\n    ```typescript\n    const score = calculateBlueprintScore({\n      aiMaturityScore: 60,\n      businessNeedScore: 80,\n      dataReadinessScore: 50,\n      processComplexityScore: 50,\n      transformationReadinessScore: 80\n    });\n    ```\n    This simulation always yields a static score of **64/100**.\n*   **Test Case Verification**: Due to the hardcoded simulation inputs, the specific banking test case (Scaling AI, Productivity + Cost Reduction + Compliance, Mostly Integrated Data, Budget Approved, 15000 employees) cannot dynamically return its targeted score of **87/100** yet. Wiring the answers to dynamic scoring multipliers is a major gap to be resolved in the Blueprint Generator implementation task.\n\n---\n\n### 7. Recommended Next Task\n1.  **Task 01 (Safety Cleanup)**: Verify routing safety cleanup. Ensure no forbidden catch-all slug leftovers exist. (Although the audit proves no catch-all routes are active, doing a formal check verifies absolute compliance).\n2.  **Task 02 (Blueprint Generator Scoring Mechanism)**: Wire the interactive blueprint quiz answers dynamically to map score multipliers according to the formula, ensuring the banking test case successfully outputs `87/100` dynamically.\n3.  **Task 03 (Explicit Public Router Pages)**: Create explicit App Router page files (such as `/industries/banking`, `/platforms`, and `/capabilities`) to bridge route gaps without dynamic slug route catch"}}
