 found that `ProductizedAssetsSection.tsx`, though imported, isn't actually being rendered. I've noted this, and it seems to be a minor import discrepancy.\n\n\n**Analyzing Tech Stack Details**\n\nI'm now taking a deeper look into the project's tech stack. I'm focusing on the Next.js and React versions, as well as the routing model, which appears to be App Router-based with explicit static files. Tailwind CSS v4 is used for styling and I've also confirmed a global premium dark mode theme, with elements like glow effects. It seems high-quality interactive components are present. I have confirmed WorldMap and Map3DEffect, and noticed that the project uses a Shancdn-like component config. Furthermore, it doesn't appear the Aceternity UI library is fully installed. I've also confirmed that the project uses the `\"motion\"` library.\n\n\n**Evaluating Blueprint Score Dynamics**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the blueprint scoring logic. The `calculateBlueprintScore` function exists, but it's hardcoded in `BuildAIEnterpriseSection.tsx`. This results in a static score, regardless of user input. Therefore, the \"banking\" test case and any other cases won't dynamically return their correct scores yet, which must be fixed in subsequent tasks.\n\n\n"}}
